## Created Files

### `bin/monitor.sh` (Linux/macOS)
### `bin/monitor.ps1` (Windows PowerShell)

Both scripts share the same behavior:

| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| **GitHub monitor** | Fetches latest 20 issues from the repo assigned to `@galaxyeye` via `gh` CLI or `GITHUB_TOKEN` env var |
| **URL monitor** | Polls a URL every N seconds; if `@galaxyeye` keyword found in response, dispatches task |
| **Task dispatch** | Saves content to a pure-digit millisecond timestamp filename → moves to `coworker/tasks/2working/` |
| **Loop/once** | Continuous loop by default; `--once` / `-Once` for single run |

### Usage

```bash
# Linux/macOS — continuous monitoring
./bin/monitor.sh --repo platonai/Browser4 --url https://example.com/tasks

# Run once (e.g. from cron)
./bin/monitor.sh --once

# Custom keyword/interval
./bin/monitor.sh --keyword "@galaxyeye" --interval 30 --url https://example.com
```

```powershell
# Windows — continuous monitoring
.\bin\monitor.ps1 -Repo platonai/Browser4 -Url https://example.com/tasks

# Run once
.\bin\monitor.ps1 -Once
```

### Authentication
- **Preferred:** `gh auth login` (uses `gh` CLI automatically)  
- **Fallback:** Set `GITHUB_TOKEN` environment variable for curl/REST API


